The paper introduces translation operators on graphs, which are relevant to graph signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GR (Graphics), which deals with graph theory and its applications. The paper also discusses the use of these operators to process signals on graphs, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the NP-Complete problem of identifying proposed translations, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these operators on random graphs, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
